*Tasks Super Eagles To Bring Back Nations’ Cup MAKURDI – Gubernatorial aspirant on the platform of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) in Benue state, Chief Ngutor Anyam has pledged to create over 20,000 sports related jobs in the state, if elected Governor in 2023. Anyam who disclosed this while speaking with newsmen in Makurdi on Sunday said similarly, he would make no fewer than 1,000 sportsmen millionaires, through sporting activities in the state. Osun APC To Party’s National Reconciliation Committee:… Fulfill Your Electoral Promises To Us, Ifon-Orolu Community… The aspirant who seeks to emerge as the standard flagbearer of the PDP in the state also charged the Super Eagles to bring back the African cup of nations to Nigeria. Anyam, a Fellow of Nigerian Institution of Estate Surveyors and Valuers further pledged to make sports the number one income earner in Benue during his administration. The aspirant also stated his desire to lighten up the three stadia in the three senatorial districts of the state; the Aper Aku stadium, Makurdi in Benue North-West senatorial district; Akume Atongo stadium, Katsina-Ala in Benue North-East senatorial district and Otukpo stadium in Benue South senatorial district. Anyam vowed to make the Aper Aku stadium an international sport centre and facility that would be utilized all year round for sporting competitions, as well as make it an academy and a hub for talent hunt in Nigeria. End.